originalText.text: Lovely place! We had a Lager and Cider with onion rings for starters. Chicken pot pie with puffy pastry and Irish chicken curry with basmati rice for the main course. Every dish is tasty, with sufficient portions for one person. The main course is about $25 per dish. Drinks were great too. Plenty of seats indoors and outdoors. Cozy, chill vibes. The service is relaxed, and slow too, so be patient, enjoy the nice open sky, looking at the park nearby after being seated. We paid about $90 with a tip for two people.

originalText.text:
Right off the subway and a two-minute walk from the tram, Granny Annie‚Äôs Bar & Kitchen has been building itself a solid reputation for its selection of beers (take it from a Belgian) and impeccable service. It is our local bar, and even if there were ten more in the island, we‚Äôd still go to Granny Annie‚Äôs for its friendly atmosphere and lovely staff.

Trivia on Wednesdays and live music on Fridays and Saturdays.

My personal favourites: Granny Annie‚Äôs Tea Time, a teapot filled with gin and tonic for two (pinky up, of course!), the smoked old-fashioned (always an Instagram-worthy moment), and the house lager, which is surprisingly good. Solid selection of Whisky too.

Food: all the pub classics, some of them with a twist, a couple of vegetarian options. Excellent weekend brunch.

Don‚Äôt miss it!
